{"id":433,"date":"2020-06-27T10:19:31","date_gmt":"2020-06-27T10:19:31","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/?p=433"},"modified":"2020-07-14T12:58:26","modified_gmt":"2020-07-14T12:58:26","slug":"5-exotic-places-to-visit-in-goa-during-monsoons","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/5-exotic-places-to-visit-in-goa-during-monsoons\/","title":{"rendered":"5 Exotic Places to visit in Goa during Monsoons"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Monsoon is the best season when you want to see nature in its brightest colours. Though Goa is famous for its sandy beaches and buzzing nightlife, it has lot many things to offer to its guests. <br>Lush greenery, pleasant weather and drizzling rains in between makes the trip to this place during monsoons a lot of fun &amp; exciting.<br>Here are some of the best exotic places to visit in Goa during monsoons<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dudhsagar falls<br><\/strong>Located in the Bhagwan Mahavir(Mollem) National Park, The Dudhsagar falls is a must-visit during monsoons. Famous for its milky white water, from it this waterfalls has got its name, flows from a huge height of 302 meters. If one visits the place during monsoons then the waters are in full flow.<br>This massive waterfall is surrounded by the dense forest of Mollem which is a home exotic flora &amp; fauna. People, both local and tourists come here to feel the bliss of nature with a gigantic waterfall and amazing lush green surrounding. Photographers favourite spot to capture nature and its splendid creation, Dudhsagar water is also considered to have medicinal properties.<br>Many travellers come here to do trekking as it the most popular activity during the monsoons. There are four trekking paths that will lead to the falls. There are few abandoned mud houses that you can use as a shelter. Make sure you take a guide along with you if it&#8217;s your first time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Savoi Spice Plantation<br><\/strong>Cloves, nutmeg, cumin, curry, cinnamon, pepper, vanilla, you name it, you will find it at Savoi Spice Plantation. Home to different kinds of Indian spice plants and fruit trees, Savoi Spice Plantation has something to interest the travellers.<br>The plantation existed two centuries back and is frequented by many tourists and locals too. The guests are given a traditional welcome and then later they are shown all kinds of spices, herbs, fruits trees. There is a pond within the vicinity where you might see exotic birds now and then.<br>The tour organised for the tourists includes a demonstration of the traditional methods of making various items from coconut and other eco-materials.<br>If anyone wants to get himself checked medically for any ailments, the plantation also has an inhouse doctor and an Ayurvedic specialist to take advice from. Visitors to this farm can also buy a variety of spices in nice gift boxes and take back home. There are accommodations available in the property for guests who want to stay back and enjoy the natural surroundings. Evening live music, folk dance programs and festive events can be arranged as per request.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dr. Salim Ali Bird Sanctuary<br><\/strong>Located on Chorao Island near the southern tip of Goa, Dr. Salim Ali bird sanctuary is spread in an area of 440 acres and is truly a paradise for bird and nature lovers.<br>The sanctuary is named after Dr. Salim Moizzudin Ali, India\u2019s pre-eminent ornithologist. One can spot rare birds and animal life. Ornithological enthusiasts can have a fun time exploring the sanctuary in a canoe. Along with birds, you might find some reptiles and crustaceans.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Mhadei River<br><\/strong>Are you an adrenaline junkie? then this is the right place for you to spend some time river rafting in the Mhadei river. During monsoons, the river swells with high water currents resulting in strong rapids making it a perfect place for river rafting. These river rafting rides are conducted by experts so one does not have to worry about the safety.<br>Passing through dense forest, the experience is amazing. Plus if it rains then the fun grows manifold.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Cotigao Wildlife Sanctuary<br><\/strong>Spread across the western ghat mountains of South Goa is the Cotigao Wildlife Sanctuary. 86 square kilometres of this vast forest area is the 2nd biggest in Goa.<br>Established in 1968, the forest was set up to conserve many floras and fauna species to preserve the rich biodiversity. While going through the dense forest of Cotigao one can spot diverse wildlife like Indian flying squirrels, mouse deer, panthers, four-horned antelopes, golden-back gliding snakes, and many species of birds and reptiles. The trees here are mostly moist-deciduous type and some evergreen trees.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A day visit to this Sanctuary is worth a trip to all the nature and wildlife lovers.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Monsoon is the best season when you want to see nature in its brightest colours. Though Goa is famous for its sandy beaches and buzzing nightlife, it has lot many things to offer to its guests. Lush greenery, pleasant weather and drizzling rains in between makes the trip to this place during monsoons a lot [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":434,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/433"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=433"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotel